<br/>Where Does This Astounding Fruit Come From?
<br/>Garcinia Cambogia grows naturally in parts of Africa, and Southeast Asia, India. The fruit varies in size similar to oranges to grapefruit. It looks like a small pumpkin with a greenish to reddish appearance. While this fruit is new to the awareness of Westerners, it has always been a part of Asian culture in meal recipes including curries. It was also noted for its filling properties. The apparent appetite-suppressant quality caught the interests of scientist who determined to investigate the element properties of the fruit.
<br/>What they found is that if the fruit is allowed to dry and cure (hence becoming brownish or black and shriveled) the rind may be used for the medicinal properties. Scientists found that the Garcinia extract is an HCA, hydroxycitric acid, that can apparently help one lose weight at a faster tempo twice, even triple, the standard rate.
